Project title. title = &ldquo;The Scalable Commutativity Rule&rdquo;
Project summary to display on homepage. summary = &ldquo;The scalable commutativity rule states that whenever interface operations commute, they have a conflict-free implementation.
The initial SOSP 2013 paper included a full formal treatment of the rule, a detailed explanation of Commuter (an automated scalability testing tool), and how we applied the rule and Commuter to build a POSIX file system and virtual memory system.
